window.bookSummaryJSON = "<h4><b>A long-hidden journal full of ancient island secrets.</b></h4><h4><b>A gathering of friends that turns into a painful goodbye.</b></h4><p>Island reporter Adele Plank now faces a multitude of choices that will directly impact her future and those closest to her—including the man she loves. Join her as she once again seeks answers to questions few have had the courage to ask even as her enemies work to keep that knowledge hidden.</p><p><b>The Book of Bloodbone</b> is the ninth riveting installment of the ongoing San Juan Islands Mystery series by USA Today featured author, D.W. Ulsterman.</p><p>______</p><p><b>\"One of the most inventive and well written books I’ve read in a very long time. So captivating!\" -Nicki Salvin Wight</b></p><p><b>\"Amazing. I love these books.\" -Heidi Thompson</b></p><p><b>\"Loving this series. The characters feel like old friends.\" -Patricia Sweet</b></p><p>______</p><p>Series Order:</p><p>-The Writer</p><p>-Dark Waters</p><p>-Murder on Matia</p><p>-Rosario’s Revenge</p><p>-Roche Harbor Rogue</p><p>-Turn Point Massacre</p><p>-Deadman Island</p><p>-The Truthing Tree</p><p>-The Book of Bloodbone</p>"; 
